<TITLE> Jamaat leader nabbed for plotting against WC trial </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Natore, April 20 (bdnews24.com)  Natore police arrested a Jamaat-e-Islami leader on Tuesday, allegedly for trying to disrupt the war crimes trial. Mir Nurul Islam, 45, press secretary of Jamaat's Natore district committee, was arrested at dawn on Tuesday from his home by members of the detective branch. Swapan Kumar Bakshi, inspector of Natore detective police told bdnews24.com that the Jamaat leader was arrested on section 54 for a secret meeting aimed to disrupt the trial of crimes against humanity during Bangladesh liberation war in 1971. He also said that they are investigating the allegation and Islam will be brought to the court on Wednesday. Delwar Hossain, principal of the City College in Natore, denied the allegation and told bdnews24.com that the Jamaat leader had come to just meet him. Mir Nurul Islan is a teacher of the college. bdnews
